net.adamcin.httpsig.ssh.jce
Class SSHRSASignature

java.lang.Object
  java.security.SignatureSpi
      java.security.Signature
          net.adamcin.httpsig.ssh.jce.SSHRSASignature

public final class SSHRSASignature
extends Signature

The "ssh-rsa" key format has the following specific encoding: string "ssh-rsa" mpint e mpint n Here the 'e' and 'n' parameters form the signature key blob. Signing and verifying using this key format is performed according to the RSASSA-PKCS1-v1_5 scheme in [RFC3447] using the SHA-1 hash. The resulting signature is encoded as follows: string "ssh-rsa" string rsa_signature_blob The value for 'rsa_signature_blob' is encoded as a string containing s (which is an integer, without lengths or padding, unsigned, and in network byte order).
